'''Al-Ahram Center for Political and Strategic Studies'''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://acpss.ahram.org.eg/eng/ |title=ACPSS |access-date=2010-02-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100107130651/http://acpss.ahram.org.eg/eng/ |archive-date=2010-01-07 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> was established in 1968 as an independent research unit functioning within the framework of [[Al-Ahram Foundation]].

The Center has evolved over time, with reforms in 1972 that broadened its research scope beyond [[Zionism]] and [[Demographics of Israel|Israeli society]] to incorporate the international and strategic issues, with a special focus on developmental issues and interactive trends between [[Arab world|Arab countries]] and the international system, the [[Middle East|regional]] framework surrounding them, and [[Arab League|amongst one another]].

The Center devotes a large part of its activities to studying the [[Demographics of Egypt|Egyptian society]] from its various [[Politics of Egypt|political]], economic, [[Egyptian Armed Forces|military]] and [[Culture of Egypt|social]] viewpoints. The center maintains complete independence in directing its research activities, and is keen on adhering to a philosophy of [[Critical thinking|criticism]]; and it aims to advance an intellectual, investigative vision for the issues at hand. It also provides for the [[freedom of speech]] of its scholars and researchers in accordance with the guidelines of [[Objectivity (science)|objectivity]] and scientific research.
The programs of the center are the result of collective efforts built on a framework of democratic scientific research planning.

