The '''Central Bank of Nigeria Act 1958''' (No 24) or '''CBN Act''' established the [[Central Bank of Nigeria]].<ref name="Mwalimu">{{Cite book|author=Mwalimu, Charles|year=2009|title=The Nigerian Legal System, Volume 2|publisher=Peter Lang|location=New York|page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=ADV5PRO7_8AC&pg=PA602 602]|isbn=978-0-8204-7855-5}}</ref> The bank commenced operations on July 1, 1959.
The Central Bank of Nigeria Act 1958 was repealed by [http://www.nigeria-law.org/CentralBankOfNigeriaDecree.htm#Miscellaneous section 54(2)] of the [[Central Bank of Nigeria Decree 1991]].<ref name="Mwalimu" /> It in turn was replaced by the [[Central Bank of Nigeria Act 2007]].<ref>{{Cite|author=Oxford Business Group|year=2010|title=The Report: Nigeria|publisher=Oxford Business Group|location=London|page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=VFONkYzHco8C&pg=PA281 281]|isbn=978-1-907065-14-9}}</ref>
