[[File:Monument of the Five Students from Strumica.jpg|thumb|A monument built in their honor, located in the public park across the city council.]] The '''Five Strumica Students''' ({{lang-mk|Петте струмички студенти}}) refers to a group of five students on the age from 20-23, all born in [[Strumica]] that on August 13, 1951 were executed by authorities in [[Communist Yugoslavia]].<ref>[http://www.promacedonia.org/44/drugi.html Гоцев, Димитър, „Новата националноосвободителна борба във Вардарска Македония 1944-1991“, София, 2000 г.] Retrieved 18 June 2018</ref> In the information report of the authorities it was stated that the group was planning to illegally cross the border to [[Greece]], but their relatives claimed that they were killed because of ideas close to [[IMRO]], an organization that fought for the independence of [[Socialist Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]].<ref>[http://www.promacedonia.org/ai/ai_17.html Пописаков, Аспарух, „От другата страна на медала (Геноцидът над македонските българи в Титова Югославия)“, в. "Македонска трибуна", САЩ, 1979 г.] Retrieved 18 June 2018</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=InyEqBVhH-EC&pg=PA183&lpg=PA183&dq=strumishkata+petorka&source=bl&ots=qU1p4UKC-Y&sig=TVKykZAjMMEhqmxpWxoepcU1uAU&hl=en&ei=c50pTMmRIoeHOOnP-bID&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CCIQ6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=strumishkata%20petorka&f=false Shea, John, „Macedonia and Greece: the struggle to define a new Balkan nation“, McFarland, USA, стр.183] Retrieved 18 June 2018</ref> At that time the Yugoslav authorities conducted a series of raids and executions to prevent the influence of the inherits of IMRO, this being one of them.<ref>[http://www.macedonian.org/About/default.asp Официален сайт на МПО, посетен на 19.06.2010 г.] Retrieved 18 June 2018</ref> ==References==
