'''Kankan Airport''' {{airport codes|KNN|GUXD|}} (or '''Kankan Diankana Airport''') is an airport serving [[Kankan]], capital of the [[Kankan Region]] in [[Guinea]]. It is {{convert|7|km}} northeast of the city, {{convert|2|km}} south of the village of Diankana.
The airport was formerly within Kankan, with the ICAO code of '''GUXN'''. The old runway is now a street in the city.
The Kankan [[non-directional beacon]] (Ident: '''KN''') is located in the city, {{convert|5.4|nmi|km|1}} southwest of the airport.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ourairports.com/navaids/KN/Kankan_NDB_GN/|title=Kankan NDB (KN) @ OurAirports|website=ourairports.com|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref>
