The '''National Insurance Court''' ({{lang-no|Trygderetten}}) is an appeals court for welfare cases in Norway.
It was established by law on 16 December 1966. Its purpose is to judge in cases where decisions by (mainly) the [[Norwegian Labour and Welfare Service]] have been appealed.<ref name=sml>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Trygderetten|first=Dag|last=Bruusgaard|encyclopedia=Store medisinske leksikon|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|editor=Nylenna, Magne|language=Norwegian|url=http://www.snl.no/.sml_artikkel/Trygderetten|accessdate=13 November 2009|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927083123/http://snl.no/.sml_artikkel/Trygderetten|archivedate=27 September 2012|df=}}</ref> Administratively, it is a part of the [[Norwegian Ministry of Labour and Social Inclusion]].<ref name=about>{{cite web|url=http://www.trygderetten.no/ikbViewer/page/om?p_lang=2|title=Om Trygderetten|publisher=National Insurance Court}}</ref>
The leader and deputy leader both need qualifications equivalent to a [[Supreme Court of Norway|Supreme Court Justice]].<ref name=sml/> The current leader is [[Knut Brofoss]], and the deputy leader is [[Trine Fernsjø]].<ref name=about/>
