{{Orphan|date=February 2009}}
{{Politics of Côte d'Ivoire}}
'''Nationalist Party''' (in [[French language|French]]: ''Parti Nationaliste''), generally referred to as '''PANA''', was an [[Côte d'Ivoire|Ivorian]] opposition group,  founded in [[Abidjan]] in 1967. It was led by Kraghé Gnagbé. PANA was immediately suppressed by the regime and Gnagbé arrested. Gnagbé had to publicly announce the non-existence of PANA.<ref>Gbagbo, Laurent: ''Côte d'Ivoire, Pour une alternative démocratique''. Paris: L'Harmattan, 1983.</ref>

