{{Infobox university | name = Taraclia State University | native_name = Universitatea de Stat din Taraclia | native_name_lang = Romanian | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | latin_name = | other_name = <!-- or: | other_names = --> | former_name = <!-- or: | former_names = --> | motto = | motto_lang = | mottoeng = | established = <!-- {{start date|YYYY}} -->1 October 2004 | closed = <!-- {{end date|YYYY}} --> | type = Public | parent = | affiliation = | religious_affiliation = | academic_affiliation = | endowment = | budget = | officer_in_charge = | chairman = | chairperson = | chancellor = | president = | vice-president = | superintendent = | provost = | vice_chancellor= | rector = | principal = | dean = | director = | head_label = | head = | academic_staff = | administrative_staff = | students = | undergrad = | postgrad = | doctoral = | other = | city = [[Taraclia]] | state = | province = | country = [[Moldova]] | coor = {{coord|45.9131|28.6706|type:edu_region:MD|display=inline,title}} | campus = | language = | free_label = | free = | colors = <!-- or: | colours = --> | athletics = | sports = | athletics_nickname = <!-- or: | athletics_nicknames = --><!-- or: | sports_nickname = --><!-- or: | sports_nicknames = --> | mascot = <!-- or: | mascots = --> | sporting_affiliations = | website = {{URL|http://tdu-tar.md/}} | logo = | footnotes = }} '''Taraclia State University''' ({{lang-ro|Universitatea de Stat din Taraclia}}) is a public university located in [[Taraclia]], [[Moldova]]. The University was opened on 1 October 2004.<ref name=4icu>{{cite web|title=Universitatea de Stat din Taraclia|url=http://www.4icu.org/reviews/13604.htm|website=4icu|accessdate=18 April 2015}}</ref><ref name=SFM>{{cite web|title=Universitatea de Stat din Taraclia|url=http://sfm.md/2014/universitatea-de-stat-din-taraclia/|publisher=SFM|accessdate=18 April 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150418041126/http://sfm.md/2014/universitatea-de-stat-din-taraclia/|archivedate=18 April 2015|df=}}</ref><ref name="Study in Europe">{{cite web|title=Taraclia State University|url=http://www.studies-in-europe.eu/s/3303/68671-Studies-in-Europe/3312-Taraclia-State-University.htm|publisher=Study in Europe|accessdate=18 April 2015}}</ref>
== History == The university was established on 1 October 2004. The then President of the Republic of Moldova [[Vladimir Voronin]] and the President of Bulgaria Georgi Parvanov attended the inaugural ceremony.<ref name=TDU>{{cite web|title=Universitatea de Stat din Taraclia|url=http://www.tdu-tar.md/|publisher=TDU|accessdate=18 April 2015|language=Russian}}</ref><ref name=Neamuri>{{cite web|title=Universitatea de Stat "Grigore Ţamblac" din Taraclia|url=http://neamuri.md/pagini/institutii-de-invatamint/universitatea-de-stat-grigore-tamblac-din-taraclia.html|publisher=Neamuri|accessdate=18 April 2015}}</ref>
== Courses == The university offers both [[undergraduate]] and [[postgraduate]] courses. Some of the topics taught at this university are—<ref name=TDU /> * Bulgarian language and literature and Romanian language and literature; * Romanian Language and Literature and English Language and Literature; * Pedagogy of primary education; * Music; * History; * Social protection services; * Accounting; * Preschool Pedagogy and the Romanian language and literature.
